If you have a converter that's female A/V audio to male eighth inch (like headphones) like this:<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.vgmusic.com/faq/gallery/adapters/a-f_StereoRCA-m_8thHP.jpg">http://www.vgmusic.com/faq/gallery/adap ... _8thHP.jpg</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Then I would just recommend plugging the NES in with an A/V cable, but put the sound cables into the converter and hook it up to your computer (if it has a microphone or line-in input). Then just record the audio coming in with something like Windows Movie Maker.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=138">Celius</a> — Fri May 01, 2009 8:25 pm</p><hr />
